 Linux SSH Authentication without roor user and password

 1. Verify User and SSH Access
 On Jump Host:
ssh tony@<app_server_1_ip>
If you can log in with a password — it’s working; we’ll now make it passwordless.

2.Generate SSH Key for user
on jump host
ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096

ls -l /home/<user>/.ssh/

3.copy the Public Key to  App Server
ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub <app serveruser>@<app_server_1_ip>

4.Verify Passwordless Access
Now test from jump host:

ssh <app serveruser>@<app_server_1_ip>
---------------------------------------------------
Task to give access from jump to app server using there keys
1. create user in app server
useradd -m -s /bin/bash vengadesh

2.Create SSH Directory for the User
mkdir -p /home/vengadesh/.ssh

3.copy your public key into authorizedkey
echo "ssh-rsa AAAAB3NzaC1yc2EAAAADAQABAAABAQDkz... your_email@example.com" >> /home/vengadesh/.ssh/authorized_keys

4.Fix permissions:
chmod 600 /home/vengadesh/.ssh/authorized_keys
chown -R vengadesh:vengadesh /home/vengadesh/.ssh
chmod 700 /home/vengadesh/.ssh
5. Test SSH from Your jump Machine
using private key
ssh -i <private key> vengadesh@hostip
